---
import Base from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Support Orbital Temple - Join the Mission">

  <main class="artwork-page">

    <!-- Main Title -->
    <h1 class="artwork-title">
      Help Build the First Radically Inclusive Temple
    </h1>

    <!-- Vision -->
    <p class="artwork-text" style="font-size: var(--text-display-sm); line-height: 1.4; text-align: center; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 3rem auto;">
      Every temple on Earth has a threshold.<br>
      Every sacred space draws a line.<br>
      <br>
      Space has no borders. No walls. No exclusions.<br>
      It belongs to every sentient being who has ever lived.
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--section-end" style="text-align: center;">
      Orbital Temple is an artistic satellite that will orbit Earth for a decade, storing names of departed beings from every corner of our planet. It is art. It is ritual. It is the first temple that truly welcomes everyone.
    </p>

    <!-- What Your Support Enables -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      What Your Support Enables
    </h2>

    <div style="display: grid; gap: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">

      <!-- Artistic -->
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Launch Art into Orbit</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          On November 28, 2025, the first purely artistic satellite from the Global South will launch from India. Your support makes history — helping send a sculpture into space that represents collective memory, radical inclusion, and the democratization of the heavens.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Educational -->
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Empower the Next Generation</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          The Quebrada Space Program teaches teenagers from the Global South how to build and launch satellites using open-source technology. Your contribution funds scholarships, workshops, and the dream that space belongs to everyone — not just those born into privilege.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Mediatic -->
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Spark a Global Conversation</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          Through exhibitions, documentaries, and a viral question — "What makes something a temple?" — this project invites humanity to reimagine the sacred. Your support amplifies this message across continents, languages, and belief systems.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Ways to Participate -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      Ways to Participate
    </h2>

    <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">

      <!-- Contribute Now -->
      <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Contribute Now</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          Make a tax-deductible donation through our fiscal sponsor, The Field. All contributions directly support the satellite launch, educational programs, and global exhibitions.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-dark); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; transition: background 0.2s ease;">
          Donate via The Field →
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Become a Partner -->
      <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Become a Partner</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          For institutions, foundations, and organizations interested in major partnerships — including naming rights, educational co-branding, and documentary co-production — let's start a conversation.
        </p>
        <a
          href="mailto:edson@edsonpavoni.com?subject=Orbital Temple Partnership Inquiry"
          style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border: 2px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
          Contact Us →
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Stay Connected -->
      <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Stay Connected</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          Follow the journey as we prepare for launch. Receive updates about exhibitions, educational initiatives, and ways to participate in this historic mission.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <a href="mailto:edson@edsonpavoni.com?subject=Orbital Temple Updates - Please Add Me" style="color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.2s ease;">
            Join our mailing list
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Current Supporters -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      With Gratitude
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      Orbital Temple is made possible by the generous support of institutions, individuals, and believers in radical inclusion:
    </p>

    <div style="margin: 2rem 0 3rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.05); border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200);">
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-display-sm); font-weight: 600; margin: 0;">
        Pearmill
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Fiscal Sponsorship Info -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      About Our Fiscal Sponsor
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      Orbital Temple operates under <strong>The Field (Performance Zone Inc.)</strong>, a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization based in New York. All U.S. contributions are tax-deductible to the extent allowed by law.
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      <strong>The Field</strong><br>
      75 Maiden Lane #906<br>
      New York, NY 10038<br>
      <a href="https://thefield.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: underline;">thefield.org</a>
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--section-end">
      When making contributions by check, please make payable to <em>Performance Zone Inc.</em> with memo: "Edson Pavoni: Orbital Temple."
    </p>

    <!-- Closing Vision -->
    <div style="text-align: center; margin: 4rem 0 3rem 0; padding: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.2); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.2);">
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-display-sm); font-style: italic; margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        "When a name ascends, it carries our collective memory.<br>
        When art ascends, it carries our hope."
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="artwork-footer">
      <Footer />
    </footer>

  </main>

</Base>
